âš™ï¸ Technical Requirements for This Dataset
1. Text Quality & Format

#Arabic NLP poses unique challenges:

1) Diacritics (ØªØ´ÙƒÙŠÙ„): Commonly removed in preprocessing to reduce noise

2) Letter Variants: Normalize different forms (e.g., â€œØ£â€, â€œØ¥â€, â€œØ¢â€ â†’ â€œØ§â€)

3) Elongations: Remove character elongations (e.g., â€œÙ…Ø¨Ø±ÙˆÙˆÙˆÙˆÙˆÙƒâ€ â†’ â€œÙ…Ø¨Ø±ÙˆÙƒâ€)

4) Mixed Scripts: Handle Arabic + Latin (e.g., short URLs, numbers)

ğŸ” The preprocessing.py file is expected to clean, normalize, and tokenize the Arabic text using tools like:

A) FarasaSegmenter (for tokenization)

B) Regex-based cleaning functions

C) NLTK or custom Arabic stemmers/normalizers

2. Class Distribution

It is critical to maintain a balanced dataset:

Smishing messages are often minority class, but you should either Use stratified sampling, Apply oversampling (e.g., SMOTE) or undersampling during training
Use class weights in the loss function.

ğŸ“Š Ideally:

50% label = 1 (Smishing)

50% label = 0 (Ham/Legitimate)

If not, report class imbalance and handle accordingly in training logic.

3. Data Volume Requirements

For deep learning to generalize well:

Model Type	Minimum Recommended Rows
CNNâ€“BiGRU Hybrid	5,000+ rows
Small Experimental	500â€“1,000 rows
Word2Vec Training	10,000+ raw sentences

ğŸ§  Note: Even if you have 2,000â€“3,000 samples, the model can learn patterns, but the risk of overfitting increases â€” apply dropout, early stopping, or k-fold CV.

ğŸ·ï¸ Labeling Considerations
Label	Meaning	Details
1	Smishing	Messages designed to deceive, e.g., phishing links, prizes, impersonation
0	Legitimate	Real-world user texts, service messages, medical reminders, etc.

Smishing messages often include:

URGENT actions ("Ù‚Ù… Ø§Ù„Ø¢Ù†", "Ø¨Ø³Ø±Ø¹Ø©")

Financial deception ("Ø±Ø¨Ø­Øª", "Ø­Ø³Ø§Ø¨Ùƒ", "Ø¨Ø·Ø§Ù‚ØªÙƒ")

Shortened or suspicious URLs

Authority impersonation ("ÙˆØ²Ø§Ø±Ø©", "Ø¨Ù†Ùƒ", "Ø´Ø±ÙƒØ© Ø§Ù„Ø§ØªØµØ§Ù„Ø§Øª")

ğŸ§ª Data Preprocessing Expected

Before feeding into the model:

Step	Purpose
Remove diacritics	Normalize script variations
Normalize Arabic letters	Reduce character diversity for consistent tokenization
Tokenize using Farasa	Tokenize Arabic correctly (respecting word roots, clitics)
Pad/truncate sequences	Make input tensors uniform 
Word2Vec embedding	Use either pre-trained or custom-trained embeddings

